This paper is primarily focused on photorealistic style transfer, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a neural architecture search method to accelerate the stylization network, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of instance normalization and skip connections, which are common techniques in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
